   294→    <div class="hero-buttons">
   295→      <a href="contact.html?program=hackathon" class="btn-primary">Register interest &rarr;</a>
   296→      <a href="#format" class="btn-secondary">See the format</a>
   297→    </div>
   298→  </div>
   299→</section>
   300→
   301→<!-- FORMAT -->
   302→<section class="format-section" id="format">
   303→  <div class="container">
   304→    <div class="section-label fade-up">The format</div>
   305→    <h2 class="section-title fade-up">10 hours of focused building.</h2>
   306→    <p class="section-sub fade-up">No slides. No pitch decks at the start. You arrive, you form a team, you build. At the end, you demo a working product to the investors in the room.</p>
   307→
   308→    <div class="timeline fade-up">
   309→      <div class="timeline-item">
   310→        <div class="timeline-time">10:00</div>
   311→        <div class="timeline-dot"><div class="timeline-dot-circle"></div><div class="timeline-dot-line"></div></div>
   312→        <div class="timeline-content">
   313→          <h3>Kickoff &amp; theme reveal</h3>
   314→          <p>The technical theme or problem space is announced. Team up, pick your angle, define your scope. You have 30 minutes to align — then you build.</p>
   315→        </div>
   316→      </div>
   317→      <div class="timeline-item">
   318→        <div class="timeline-time">10:30</div>
   319→        <div class="timeline-dot"><div class="timeline-dot-circle"></div><div class="timeline-dot-line"></div></div>
   320→        <div class="timeline-content">
   321→          <h3>Building begins</h3>
   322→          <p>Heads down. Real code, real infrastructure, real product. Mentors from our sponsor network are in the room to unblock you when you're stuck.</p>
   323→        </div>
   324→      </div>
   325→      <div class="timeline-item">
   326→        <div class="timeline-time">13:00</div>
   327→        <div class="timeline-dot"><div class="timeline-dot-circle"></div><div class="timeline-dot-line"></div></div>
   328→        <div class="timeline-content">
   329→          <h3>Lunch + mid-day check-in</h3>
   330→          <p>Break, eat, recalibrate. Optional 5-minute mid-day check-ins with a mentor if you've hit a wall or want to pressure-test your approach.</p>
   331→        </div>
   332→      </div>
   333→      <div class="timeline-item">
   334→        <div class="timeline-time">14:00</div>
   335→        <div class="timeline-dot"><div class="timeline-dot-circle"></div><div class="timeline-dot-line"></div></div>
   336→        <div class="timeline-content">
   337→          <h3>Back to building</h3>
   338→          <p>Afternoon block. Focus on making it work end-to-end, not just look good. A working demo matters more than a polished UI.</p>
   339→        </div>
   340→      </div>
   341→      <div class="timeline-item">
   342→        <div class="timeline-time">18:00</div>
   343→        <div class="timeline-dot"><div class="timeline-dot-circle"></div><div class="timeline-dot-line"></div></div>
   344→        <div class="timeline-content">
   345→          <h3>Freeze + prep demos</h3>
   346→          <p>Code freeze. Two hours to prep your demo — no new features, just make it presentable and tell the story clearly.</p>
   347→        </div>
   348→      </div>
   349→      <div class="timeline-item">
   350→        <div class="timeline-time">19:00</div>
   351→        <div class="timeline-dot"><div class="timeline-dot-circle"></div><div class="timeline-dot-line"></div></div>
   352→        <div class="timeline-content">
   353→          <h3>Demo + investor pitches</h3>
   354→          <p>Each team gets 5 minutes. Live demo, one slide max. Sponsors ask real questions. The best teams get follow-up conversations, not just a prize.</p>
   355→        </div>
   356→      </div>
   357→      <div class="timeline-item">
   358→        <div class="timeline-time">20:00</div>
   359→        <div class="timeline-dot"><div class="timeline-dot-circle"></div><div class="timeline-dot-line"></div></div>
   360→        <div class="timeline-content">
   361→          <h3>Awards + networking</h3>
   362→          <p>Prizes, credits, and introductions. More importantly: the people in this room are who you want to know.</p>
   363→        </div>
   364→      </div>
   365→    </div>
   366→  </div>
   367→</section>
   368→
   369→<!-- WHO ATTENDS -->
   370→<section>
   371→  <div class="container">
   372→    <div class="section-label fade-up">Who attends</div>
   373→    <h2 class="section-title fade-up">Built for people who ship.</h2>
   374→    <p class="section-sub fade-up">This isn't a general hackathon. We select for technical ability and the drive to build real things — not to win competitions.</p>
   375→
   376→    <div class="who-grid">
   377→      <div class="who-card fade-up">
   378→        <div class="who-card-icon">⚡</div>
   379→        <h3>Technical founders</h3>
   380→        <p>You've already shipped something. You build fast. You want a focused day with peers at your level and direct access to investors who get technical products.</p>
   381→      </div>
   382→      <div class="who-card fade-up">
   383→        <div class="who-card-icon">🛠</div>
   384→        <h3>Developers exploring startups</h3>
   385→        <p>You're a strong engineer who's been thinking about building your own thing. This is a low-stakes way to test if you like the founder experience.</p>
   386→      </div>
   387→      <div class="who-card fade-up">
   388→        <div class="who-card-icon">🎓</div>
   389→        <h3>CS &amp; engineering students</h3>
